obster-british-independent-film-awards-nominations |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=3 November 2015}}</ref>\n| [[BIFA Award for Best British Independent Film|Best British Independent Film]]\n| ''Amy''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| [[Asif Kapadia]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Documentary\n| Asif Kapadia and [[James Gay-Rees]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Producer of the Year\n| James Gay-Rees\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Craft\n| Chris King\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Broadcast Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| Best Documentary Feature\n| ''Amy''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2015 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes Film Festival]]\n| [[L'\u0152il d'or]]\n| ''Amy''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Queer Palm]]\n| ''Amy''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n||[[Chicago Film Critics Association]]<ref>{{cite web |title='Mad Max: Fury Road' Leads The Race For 2015 CFCA Awards |url=http://www.chicagofilmcritics.org/awards/140-mad-max-lead-2015-cfca-awards |date=14 December 2015 |website=Chicago Film Critics Association |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222093417/http://www.chicagofilmcritics.org/awards/140-mad-max-lead-2015-cfca-awards/ |archivedate=22 December 2015 }}</ref>\n| [[Chicago Film Critics Association Award for Best Documentary|Best Documentary]]\n| ''Amy''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n||[[Critics' Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Critics' Choice Awards Nominations: 'Mad Max' Leads Film; ABC, HBO, FX Networks & 'Fargo' Top TV |url=http://deadline.com/2015/12/critics-choice-awards-nominations-2016-full-list-1201666326/ \n|first=Patrick |last=Hipes |date=14 December 2015 |website=Deadline}}</ref>\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Documentary Feature|Best Documentary Feature]]\n| ''Amy''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|[[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Dallas-Fort Worth Film Critics Name \"Spotlight\" Best Picture of 2015 |url=http://www.dfwcritics.com/dallas-fort-worth-film-critics-name-spotlight-best-picture-of-2015/ |date=14 December 2015 |website